<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - CYLINDER SLEEVE
        REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CYLINDER SLEEVE REMOVAL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use the universal wet sleeve puller
                    <emph type="bold">SE-2536</emph>
                    to remove the cylinder sleeves as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_106.xml" xrefid="ef4150610">6.10</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>PRIOR TO INSTALLING THE PULLER, BAR THE ENGINE OVER SO THE CRANKSHAFT JOURNAL IS LOCATED
                            AT THE BOTTOM (LOW POINT) OF ITS TRAVEL. THIS PREVENTS POSSIBLE DAMAGE TO THE JOURNAL BY THE
                            PULLER LIFTING JAWS DURING PULLER INSTALLATION.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position the puller in the sleeve and spread the lifting jaws so the tangs grip the
                        bottom of the sleeve.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">With the lifting bridge firmly on the crankcase top deck, turn the forcing nut to
                        break the cylinder sleeve loose from the crankcase.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lift the sleeve and puller from the crankcase.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove sleeve from puller and mark the sleeve with its cylinder bore number and
                        position in relation to the camshaft for purposes of inspection and reassembly.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
